This paper is about an algorithm for solving imperfect information games, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm involves updating values in a way that alternates between different players, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses theoretical upper bounds on solution error, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
